Spark
```json
{
"application": "Spark",
"other_software": [
"Hadoop",
"Moab"
],
"resource_requirements": {
"JAVA_HOME": "/usr/lib/jvm/jre-1.8.0/",
"MAGPIE_PYTHON": "/usr/bin/python",
"HADOOP_SETUP": "yes",
"HADOOP_SETUP_TYPE": "YARN",
"HADOOP_VERSION": "3.2.2",
"HADOOP_HOME": "${HOME}/hadoop-${HADOOP_VERSION}",
"HADOOP_LOCAL_DIR": "/tmp/${USER}/hadoop",
"SPARK_SETUP": "yes",
"SPARK_SETUP_TYPE": "YARN",
"SPARK_VERSION": "3.0.3-bin-hadoop3.2",
"SPARK_HOME": "${HOME}/spark-${SPARK_VERSION}",
"SPARK_LOCAL_DIR": "/tmp/${USER}/spark"
},
"notes": "The script appears to be running a Spark job within a Hadoop environment. It makes extensive use of environment variables to configure various aspects of the setup and execution of Spark and Hadoop. The script relies on the Moab resource manager and leverages PDSH (Parallel Distributed Shell) for distributed execution. It includes options for various job types, configurations, and settings, such as Terasort, SparkPi, SparkWordCount, HDFS, and more."
}
```
